  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study was to evaluate the effect of a dental water jet on initial
      peri-implant disease resolution.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Peri-implant disease is becoming more frequent during the last decade. Till today, there is
      no effective evidence-based treatment. The use of water-jet might improve those situations
      and reduce morbidity and implant loss.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
